FBIS4-56565 "drlat088_a_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-088 Daily Report 6 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Chilean Parties Advocate Cooperation Chilean Parties Advocate Cooperation FL0605021594 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 6 May 94 FL0605021594 Havana Cuba Vision Network Spanish BFN [Text] The two main parties that comprise the government coalition in Chile advocate official plans to increase ties of cooperation with Cuba. Gutenberg Martinez, president of the Christian Democratic Party, asserted that his organization has a positive view toward any effort that could signify solidarity with the Cuban people. Socialist Party President Camilo Escalona expressed his belief that the upcoming Ibero-American Summit represents a good opportunity for Chile to substantiate its plan of cooperation with Cuba.
